content.problemStatement:
Toad has been asked to plan the next trip in Mushroom World. To do this, he is required to solve the following problem, can you help him?

Given a tree with NNN nodes, a Depth-first search function for it is defined below.

`vector adj[N+1];
int tin[N+1];
int timer = 0;

void DFS(int U, int P) {
    tin[U] = timer++;
    sort(adj[U].begin(), adj[U].end());
    for (int V: adj[U])
        if (V != P)
            DFS(V, U);
}
`You are asked QQQ queries of the form:


A&nbsp;XA \space XA&nbsp;X: Given positive integers AAA and XXX, find an integer BBB (1≤B≤N1 \leq B \leq N1≤B≤N), such that, if we start the Depth-first search from node AAA, `tin[B] = X`.
